git-hop is a context-aware porcelain tool for managing
Git worktrees, Docker environments, and structured workspaces.

Clone Mode:
  git-hop <uri> [path]
  Clones a repository using bare repo + worktree structure (recommended)
  Configure default behavior via global config: bareRepo setting

Worktree Mode:
  git-hop <branch>
  Inside a project root: create/sync worktree for a branch

Usage:
  git-hop [flags]
  git-hop [command]

Available Commands:
  add         Add a new worktree and environment
  doctor      Check and repair the environment
  env         Manage the environment lifecycle
  init        Initialize git-hop repository structure
  list        List all managed worktrees
  merge       Merge a worktree branch into a receiving branch, then delete the source worktree
  move        Rename a worktree and its branch
  prune       Remove orphaned worktrees and hubs from state
  remove      Remove a hub, hopspace, or branch
  status      Show the working tree status

Flags:
      --branch string       branch name for fork-attach mode
      --config string       config file (default is $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/git-hop/config.json)
      --dry-run             preview changes without applying
      --force               bypass safety checks
      --format string       Output format (table, json, yaml) (default "table")
      --git-domain string   Git domain for shorthand notation (e.g., github.com, gitlab.com)
  -g, --global              use global hopspace in $GIT_HOP_DATA_HOME (default: local)
  -h, --help                help for git-hop
      --json                output in JSON format
      --no-color            Disable ANSI colour
      --no-hints            Suppress next-step hints after command output
      --porcelain           machine-readable output
  -q, --quiet               Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose             verbose output
      --version             version for git-hop

Use "git-hop [command] --help" for more information about a command.
